Two brothers have been killed by suspected kidnappers who invaded Ajowa Akoko community in Akoko North West Local Government Area The kidnappers abducted two other children in the community. Witnesses said the kidnappers stormed the community about 1am and gained entrance to the home of one Alhaji Yekini Oludotun after shooting intermitently. It was gathered that the intervention of a senior army officer in the area helped to stop the kidnappers who fled to another area. The kidnappers were said to have killed two sons of one Mr. Dele in another area and abducted two children. A source in the community said security agents have started combing the forest with a view to fishing out the criminals. Ondo Police spokesman, ASP Tee-Leo Ikoro, confirmed the incident at Ajowa and said policemen are on the trail of the criminals.